uity, with a particular focus not just on the texts in their original contexts, but also on how they were interpreted and exploited for both literary and more broadly cultural purposes later in antiquity. Taken together, the essays sketch a picture of a continuous tradition of critical and historical engagement with the literature of the past from the period of Aristophanes and then Plato and Aristotle in classical Athens to the rich prose literature of the Second Sophistic. Richard Hunter's earlier essays are collected in On Coming After (Berlin 2008).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aClassical literaturexHistory and criticism. 4aAntike. 4aLiteratur. 4aTextkritik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aantiquity.  acriticism.  aliterature.1 aKarakasis, Evangelos, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRengakos, Antonios, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021 Englishz978311075405608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021z9783110753813oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831107477680 cprintz978311074756040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311074757740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110747577423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110747577/original  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075405-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2021